take this iconic red chair

00:02:04.880 --> 00:02:06.860
places that we could have
never imagined.

00:02:06.860 --> 00:02:09.455
And that is the creativity
of this campaign.

00:02:09.455 --> 00:02:10.860
ANDREW BOSWORTH: People who
aren't necessarily a part of

00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:14.080
the process, that's a loss for
not just the rest of us who

00:02:14.080 --> 00:02:16.420
don't get that perspective, but
also for them who don't

00:02:16.420 --> 00:02:19.130
get to shape the future that
is going to come to exist.

00:02:19.130 --> 00:02:20.520
COLLEEN BLAKE: This isn't
just a company

00:02:20.520 --> 00:02:22.090
versus company issue.

00:02:22.090 --> 00:02:24.480
It's a societal issue that
we're trying to change.

00:02:24.480 --> 00:02:26.000
LUCINDA SANDERS: At the end of
the day, we'll know Sit With

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:30.470
Me's successful if we have
created a conversation around

00:02:30.470 --> 00:02:33.530
the importance of women's
participation in computing.

00:02:33.530 --> 00:02:36.655
