experience with them.

00:06:39.690 --> 00:06:42.310
SUSAN WOJCICKI: So I
joined first as the

00:06:42.310 --> 00:06:43.560
first marketing person.

00:06:43.560 --> 00:06:47.530
And at the time, I
had very little

00:06:47.530 --> 00:06:49.130
practical experiences marketing.

00:06:49.130 --> 00:06:49.890
I had a degree.

00:06:49.890 --> 00:06:51.400
I had an MBA.

00:06:51.400 --> 00:06:54.380
So I can't really say there
was any one thing that

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:55.070
prepared me.

00:06:55.070 --> 00:06:58.130
It was definitely working,
like I grew

00:06:58.130 --> 00:06:59.550
as the company grew.

00:06:59.550 --> 00:07:01.400
And I took on new challenges.

00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:04.110
There was always new things that
I thought I wasn't really

00:07:04.110 --> 00:07:04.850
sure I could do.

00:07:04.850 --> 00:07:06.570
I had never really
done them before.

00:07:06.570 --> 00:07:09.470
But each time I did them, I kept
building that skill set.

00:07:09.470 --> 00:07:12.290
And so over the course
of the last--

00:07:12.290 --> 00:07:14.610
it's been 13 years that
I've been at Google--

00:07:14.610 --> 00:07:17.350
I've been able to build a
really great skill set.

00:07:17.350 --> 00:07:21.250
So I will say my first job was
being a product manager at a

00:07:21.250 --> 00:07:22.440
small little start-up.

00:07:22.440 --> 00:07:26.840
And I really got the passion for
technology there and the

00:07:26.840 --> 00:07:30.470
passion for building products.

00:07:30.470 --> 00:07:33.240
And I learned by being at that
company that you needed to be

00:07:33.240 --> 00:07:35.190
more than a technologist though,
that you also had to

00:07:35.190 --> 00:07:36.990
have some business skills,
because the company went out

00:07:36.990 --> 00:07:39.120
of business.

00:07:39.120 --> 00:07:41.450
Even though I thought I
built a great product.

00:07:41.450 --> 00:07:43.400
And so then I got interested
in also

00:07:43.400 --> 00:07:44.650
building business skills.

00:07:47.550 --> 00:07:48.490
ANGELA LAI: I'll piggyback
on that.

00:07:48.490 --> 00:07:52.220
The Google culture, it's a
very supportive culture.

00:07:52.220 --> 00:07:54.190
And we really believe in
lifetime learning.

00:07:54.190 --> 00:07:58.780
And at the company, both
informal and formal, we have

00:07:58.780 --> 00:08:01.110
classes to help people get
through things much like we go

00:08:01.110 --> 00:08:01.610
through school.

00:08:01.610 --> 00:08:05.460
And at the same time, as a
company, we always try to

00:08:05.460 --> 00:08:08.040
shoot for really ambitious
projects.

00:08:08.040 --> 00:08:10.560
And that's the way to stretch
ourselves, to

00:08:10.560 --> 00:08:12.200
make ourselves learn.

00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:13.870
And we always try different
things.

00:08:13.870 --> 00:08:15.410
We're constantly trying
different things.

00:08:15.410 --> 00:08:19.940
And the culture of experiment is
there and available for us.

00:08:19.940 --> 00:08:24.680
And so for me, at Google, it's
a lifetime of learning, just

00:08:24.680 --> 00:08:27.850
continue to better ourselves.

