a problem is definitely

00:08:57.400 --> 00:09:00.820
one that I really value,
because it helps

00:09:00.820 --> 00:09:03.358
us get stuff done.

00:09:03.358 --> 00:09:05.593
GAYATRI RAJAN: So my
early experience--

00:09:05.593 --> 00:09:06.820
it may not be early for you.

00:09:06.820 --> 00:09:08.500
It was early for me.

00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:11.550
I became a mother
in my early 20s.

00:09:11.550 --> 00:09:15.510
And in many ways, that prepared
me for the career

00:09:15.510 --> 00:09:16.300
that followed.

00:09:16.300 --> 00:09:19.060
Because as a mother, I had to
learn-- one of the first

00:09:19.060 --> 00:09:22.160
things you have to learn is to
give up control, to go with

00:09:22.160 --> 00:09:27.900
the flow, to seek opportunities
where they may

00:09:27.900 --> 00:09:33.650
arise, rather than having
a very strict plan.

00:09:33.650 --> 00:09:36.580
It also taught me how to
multi-task, because I had to.

00:09:36.580 --> 00:09:40.530
But I think, more importantly,
most importantly, it taught me

00:09:40.530 --> 00:09:44.180
to really care about the
work that I was doing.

00:09:44.180 --> 00:09:45.320
Because it matters.

00:09:45.320 --> 00:09:47.720
It matters when you have
something else

00:09:47.720 --> 00:09:48.970
you could do instead.

00:09:51.010 --> 00:09:52.090
It really focuses you.

00:09:52.090 --> 00:09:54.810
It makes you want to do
something even better than

00:09:54.810 --> 00:09:56.880
what you might have
wanted to before.

00:09:56.880 --> 00:09:59.830
And I think you need
that passion.

00:09:59.830 --> 00:10:00.960
You need that flexibility.

00:10:00.960 --> 00:10:04.160
And you need the ability
to just manage 100

00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:05.790
things at once at Google.

00:10:05.790 --> 00:10:07.550
And I think it's--

00:10:07.550 --> 00:10:11.100
my children taught me how
to survive this place.

00:10:11.100 --> 00:10:13.980
MEGAN SMITH: I think, we've been
working in the tech world

00:10:13.980 --> 00:10:15.840
so much, that you know,
start-ups are like that.

00:10:15.840 --> 00:10:17.070
They're just like
a free for all.

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:18.410
And it's just coming at you.

00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:20.480
And you just have to try to
rise to the occasion.

00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:22.370
So that's I think a pretty
good example.

00:10:22.370 --> 00:10:24.950
There's a great book that
Alice Walker wrote.

00:10:24.950 --> 00:10:27.310
It's called We Are the Ones
We've Been Waiting For.

00:10:27.310 --> 00:10:29.785
And I think about the
things you guys

00:10:29.785 --> 00:10:32.160
have said about Google.

00:10:32.160 --> 00:10:33.470
It's our company.

00:10:33.470 --> 00:10:36.510
And we just have to make it
what it's going to be.

00:10:36.510 --> 00:10:39.120
And I think that if you're in
a start-up or in a larger

00:10:39.120 --> 00:10:43.150
